# Database Patterns

## SQLAlchemy/SQLModel Models

```python
from sqlmodel import SQLModel, Field
from datetime import datetime
from uuid import uuid4

class Publication(SQLModel, table=True):
    __tablename__ = "publications"

    id: int | None = Field(default=None, primary_key=True)
    doi: str | None = Field(default=None, unique=True, index=True)
    pmid: str | None = Field(default=None, unique=True, index=True)
    title: str = Field(index=True)
    abstract: str | None = None
    authors: list[str] = Field(default_factory=list, sa_type=ARRAY(String))
    source: str  # "pubmed", "openalex", "clinicaltrials"
    published_date: datetime | None = None
    created_at: datetime = Field(default_factory=datetime.utcnow)
    updated_at: datetime = Field(default_factory=datetime.utcnow)
```

## Async Session Setup

```python
from sqlalchemy.ext.asyncio import create_async_engine, async_sessionmaker, AsyncSession

engine = create_async_engine(settings.DATABASE_URL, echo=False, pool_size=20)
async_session = async_sessionmaker(engine, class_=AsyncSession, expire_on_commit=False)

async def get_db() -> AsyncGenerator[AsyncSession, None]:
    async with async_session() as session:
        yield session
```

## Repository Pattern

```python
class PublicationRepository:
    def __init__(self, session: AsyncSession):
        self.session = session

    async def get_by_doi(self, doi: str) -> Publication | None:
        stmt = select(Publication).where(Publication.doi == doi)
        result = await self.session.execute(stmt)
        return result.scalar_one_or_none()

