## Alembic Migrations

- Config: `alembic/env.py` with async engine
- Generate: `alembic revision --autogenerate -m "description"`
- Apply: `alembic upgrade head`
- Always review autogenerated migrations before applying
- One migration per logical change — don't batch unrelated schema changes

## Rules

1. All DB access goes through repositories — never raw queries in services
2. Use `AsyncSession` everywhere — no sync sessions
3. Use `select()` (2.0 style) — never `session.query()` (legacy)
4. Transactions: let the session auto-commit, explicit `session.commit()` in repos
5. Indexes on frequently queried columns (doi, pmid, title, source)
